 rac{-R h c}{n_{f}^{2}}{/tex} If {tex}
u{/tex} is the frequency of emitted radiation, we get {tex}
u{/tex} = {tex} rac{E_{i}-E_{f}}{h}{/tex} {tex}
u{/tex} = {tex} rac{-R ch}{n_{i}^{2}}{/tex} - {tex}\left( rac{-R ch}{n_{f}^{2}}ight){/tex} = Rch {tex}\left[ rac{1}{n_{f}^{2}}- rac{1}{n_{i}^{2}}ight]{/tex} = {tex} rac{m e^{4}}{8 \varepsilon_{0}^{2} h^{2}}{/tex} {tex}\left[ rac{1}{n_{f}^{2}}- rac{1}{n_{i}^{2}}ight]{/tex} This is the required expression. If electron jumps from n i = 4 to n f = 3, 2, 1, radiation belongs to Paschen, Balmer and Lyman series.

